# Vercel Web Analytics Installation

Successfully installed and configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Next.js project.

## Changes Made

### 1. Package Installation
- Installed `@vercel/analytics` package (version 1.4.1)
- Updated `package.json` and `package-lock.json` accordingly

### 2. Code Configuration
Modified `app/layout.tsx`:
- Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from "@vercel/analytics/next";`
- Added `<Analytics />` component at the end of the body element, after `<PwaRegistrar />`

### 3. Build Artifacts
- Updated `public/sw.js` - service worker file regenerated during build process

## Implementation Details

The implementation follows the official Vercel documentation (fetched from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart):
- Used the Next.js App Router integration pattern
- Placed the Analytics component in the root layout file
- Component is positioned at the end of the body, preserving existing structure

The Analytics component will automatically:
- Track page views
- Collect visitor data
- Send analytics to Vercel dashboard when deployed

## Testing

✅ TypeScript compilation passed with no errors (`npm run typecheck`)
✅ Production build completed successfully (`npm run build`)
✅ All 25 routes generated without issues
✅ No new linting errors introduced by the changes

## Next Steps

To enable analytics collection:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Enable Web Analytics in the Vercel dashboard under the Analytics section
3. Analytics will automatically begin collecting data once deployed

## Notes

- The Analytics component is lightweight and won't impact page performance
- No additional configuration is needed in development mode
- Analytics data will only be collected in production deployments on Vercel
- The existing PWA registrar and theme provider components remain unaffected
